<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="127" type="distribution and taxonomic notes">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="127">Distribution and taxonomic notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="127">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Efetov &amp; Hofmann &amp; Tarmann &amp; Tremewan" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. azurea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="azurea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="127">Zygaena rhadamanthus azurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed in the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="départements">departements</normalizedToken>
of Var and Alpes-Maritimes (excluding coastal regions). Although 
<bibRefCitation author="Leraut, P" journalOrPublisher="NAP Editions, Verrieres-le Buisson" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" refId="B20" refString="Leraut, P, 2012. Volume 3: Moths of Europe, Zygaenids, Pyralids 1 and Brachodids. NAP Editions, Verrieres-le Buisson" title="Volume 3: Moths of Europe, Zygaenids, Pyralids 1 and Brachodids." year="2012">Leraut (2012</bibRefCitation>
: 98) synonymised this taxon with the melanistic 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burgeff" authorityYear="1914" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. stygia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="stygia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="127">Zygaena rhadamanthus stygia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Burgeff, 1914, the distribution of the latter ranges from east of the River Var (Alpes-Maritimes) in France to Imperia in Italy. Much has been written about littoral melanism (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Burgeff, H" journalOrPublisher="Biologisches Zentralblatt" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" pagination="1 - 23" refId="B4" refString="Burgeff, H, 1951. Die Meearalpengrenze der Zygaenen (Lep.), eine mit Hilfe der Populationsanalyse der Arten der Gattung Zygaena (Lepidoptera) durchgefuehrte Untersuchung ueber die Lokalisation und die Bedeutung geographischer Rassen in ihrem Zusammenhang mit der Eiszeit. Biologisches Zentralblatt 70: 1 - 23" title="Die Meearalpengrenze der Zygaenen (Lep.), eine mit Hilfe der Populationsanalyse der Arten der Gattung Zygaena (Lepidoptera) durchgefuehrte Untersuchung ueber die Lokalisation und die Bedeutung geographischer Rassen in ihrem Zusammenhang mit der Eiszeit." volume="70" year="1951">Burgeff 1951</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Burgeff, H" journalOrPublisher="Nova Acta Leopoldina (NF)" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" pagination="1 - 59" refId="B5" refString="Burgeff, H, 1956. Ueber die Modifizierbarkeit von Arten und geographischen Rassen der Gattung Zygaena (Lep.). Nova Acta Leopoldina (NF) 18 (127): 1 - 59" title="Ueber die Modifizierbarkeit von Arten und geographischen Rassen der Gattung Zygaena (Lep.)." volume="18" year="1956">1956</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Burgeff, H" journalOrPublisher="Mathematisch-physikalische Klasse)" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" pagination="1 - 15" refId="B6" refString="Burgeff, H, 1965. Ueber die Bestimmung systematischer Einheiten durch morphologische und physiologische Merkmale, dargestellt an der Gattung Zygaena (Lep.) Nachrichten der Akademie der Wissenschaften in Goettingen (II. Mathematisch-physikalische Klasse) 1965: 1 - 15" title="Ueber die Bestimmung systematischer Einheiten durch morphologische und physiologische Merkmale, dargestellt an der Gattung Zygaena (Lep.) Nachrichten der Akademie der Wissenschaften in Goettingen (II." volume="1965" year="1965">1965</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dujardin, F" journalOrPublisher="90 e Congres des Societes Savantes" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" pagination="585 - 596" refId="B7" refString="Dujardin, F, 1965. Les voies de penetration des Lepidopteres dans le departement des Alpes-Maritimes. 90e Congres des Societes Savantes 2: 585 - 596" title="Les voies de penetration des Lepidopteres dans le departement des Alpes-Maritimes." volume="2" year="1965">Dujardin 1965</bibRefCitation>
: 586-587) and that exhibited by subsp. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burgeff" authorityYear="1914" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="subsp. stygia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="stygia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="127">stygia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a good example for comparison with the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="‘normal’">'normal'</normalizedToken>
phenotype of subsp. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Efetov &amp; Hofmann &amp; Tarmann &amp; Tremewan" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="subsp. azurea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="azurea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="127">azurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- to consider both taxa as one subspecies clearly disregards the concept of littoral melanism and the zoogeography of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Esper" baseAuthorityYear="1789" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhadamanthus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="127">Zygaena rhadamanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in south-eastern France. Consequently, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Efetov &amp; Hofmann &amp; Tarmann &amp; Tremewan" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. azurea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="azurea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="127">Zygaena rhadamanthus azurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here reinstated as a valid subspecies (
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="127">stat. rev.</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
